FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to commonly asked questions about our space and time data platform
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_1: What kind of space and time data does your platform provide?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our platform offers a comprehensive collection of data related to space exploration, astronomical observations, and precise timekeeping. This includes satellite telemetry, celestial mapping, orbital mechanics calculations, and atomic clock measurements.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: How accurate is the time data?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: We utilize cutting-edge atomic clocks and specialized time transfer techniques to ensure our time data is accurate to within nanoseconds of international timekeeping standards.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: Can I access historical space data?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Yes, our platform provides access to archival data spanning decades of space exploration missions, astronomical observations, and time measurements. You can query and analyze this historical data for research or analysis purposes.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: What formats are the data available in?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: We offer data in industry-standard formats such as FITS for astronomical data, CSV and JSON for tabular data, and custom APIs for seamless integration with your applications.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: Can I contribute my own data to the platform?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Absolutely! We welcome contributions from the scientific community, amateur astronomers, and space enthusiasts. Our platform has a data ingestion pipeline that allows you to submit your own space and time data for inclusion in our database.

PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Space and Time Data
ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: What kind of space and time data does this app provide?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Our app offers a wide range of data related to space exploration and astronomical events, including satellite trajectories, celestial body positions, orbital mechanics calculations, and timelines of key space milestones.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: How is the data sourced and verified?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: We aggregate data from authoritative sources like space agencies, observatories, and scientific databases. Our team of experts meticulously verifies and cross-checks the data for accuracy and consistency.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: Can I access historical data or is it only real-time?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: You can access both real-time and historical data through our app. We maintain extensive archives of past space events and observations dating back several decades.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Is there an API or can I only view the data through the app?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Yes, we provide a robust API that allows you to integrate our space and time data directly into your own applications and systems. Check our documentation for API access and usage details.
